As he was arguing the case against Chevron in Ecuador back in 2009, the company expressly said its long-term strategy was to demonize him.
And, as Donziger’s lawyer has pointed out, the firm Kaplan chose, Seward & Kissel, likely has ties to Chevron.
Photo: Dolores Ochoa/APA Tainted Witness Despite Donziger’s current predicament, the case against Chevron in Ecuador was a spectacular victory.
Even though the ruling was subsequently upheld by the Ecuadorian Supreme Court, Chevron immediately made clear that it would not be paying the judgment.
That choice has set the stage for the legal losses Donziger has suffered since, according to some close watchers of the Chevron case.